# Rule: No Brackets for Early Return

**Description:**
For early returns (such as `if (!foo) return ...;`), do not use curly brackets. The return statement should be on the same line as the if statement, without braces.

## Examples

✅ Allowed:
```js
if (!foo) return null;
if (error) return handleError();
```

❌ Not allowed:
```js
if (!foo) {
  return null;
}
if (error) {
  return handleError();
}
``` 